venue.name: Parklane Zha Yun Tun Mee House

tip.text: Creative menu!
Check out their Torched Mars waffles! The marshmallow is toasted just to the right texture, and the waffles is one of the best eaten! Perfect coupled with the ice-cream!
The banchan here is tasty! Especially the beansprouts! And it's free flow! The service is slightly slow though. The army stew is very flavourful as well! Definitely recommend it for boy outing!
The Ramen has very little meat inside. Discouraged!
Recommend the famous hundred years Hakka noodles! The noodles taste a bit blend, but the soup and ingredients are solid good. Prawns, meat ball, and tofu!
Service not friendly. But food come relatively fast. Curry chicken noodles is decent! Discouraged Kaya toast, the Kaya is not evenly spread.
Don't miss out the Christmas games booth! And also the Christmas market stall!
